-- S.Korea raises $280 mln from sale of IBK shares
-- By Joyce Lee
-- Thu Dec 04, 2014 08:01PM EST
-- None



SEOUL, Dec 5 (Reuters) - South Korea said it raised 310.8 billion won ($279.55 million) from its block sale of 21 million shares in Industrial Bank of Korea <024110.KS> on Friday.

The government, through the Ministry of Strategy and Finance, said in a statement it sold the 3.8 percent stake at 14,800 won per share.